pve-microvm (0.1.17-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Switch to PCIe + non-transitional virtio devices.
  * QEMU 10.x microvm mmio transport has a device probe bug — only virtio-blk
    binds on the mmio bus. PCIe mode works reliably for all devices.
  * Revert virtio drivers to built-in (=y) — no initrd needed with PCI.
  * Template: no initrd, root=/dev/vda, direct kernel boot.

 -- Rui Carmo <rui.carmo@gmail.com>  Sat, 19 Apr 2026 18:30:00 +0000

pve-microvm (0.1.16-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix: make virtio_blk a module too so initrd handles ALL device setup.
  * Remove root= from kernel cmdline — initrd mounts root after loading modules.
  * This forces the kernel to use the initrd, loading all virtio modules.

 -- Rui Carmo <rui.carmo@gmail.com>  Sat, 19 Apr 2026 17:30:00 +0000

pve-microvm (0.1.15-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix: add rdinit=/init to kernel cmdline when using initrd.
  * Without this, kernel bypasses initrd and mounts root directly,
    so virtio modules never load.
  * Add grep/dmesg/cat/ls/ip to initrd busybox symlinks.

 -- Rui Carmo <rui.carmo@gmail.com>  Sat, 19 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0000

